		<h2>Road Closure Information</h2>
			<div class="entry">
				<p><strong>Common Road Closure Information</strong></p>
<p>The following are roads that could be closed due to weather in the mornings. Students may be brought to another stop, to the end of the road or to an open intersection to catch their Bus or to Sams Valley Elementary or Hanby, by 8:15 AM, to catch Buses into Crater or Hanby. If we close roads in the morning, they will remain closed for both HS/MS and Elementary routes. Radio and TV will report any road closures starting at 6:00 AM. It is our intention to transport all students home in the afternoon even if there has been a closure in the morning. Weather/roads will rarely be bad enough in the afternoon to keep roads closed.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>*Roads could remain closed in PM if conditions have worsened or not improved.*</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>FOR CLOSURE INFO: STAY TUNED TO RADIO AND TV STATIONS, </strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>CONTACT YOUR SCHOOL OR CHECK THE DISTRICT WEBSITE</strong></p>
<p>Commonly closed Sams Valley roads</p>
<ul>
<li> All of E. Evans Creek Road</li>
<li>Antioch Road ABOVE Jones Road</li>
<li>Meadows Road ABOVE Sweet Lane</li>
<li>Ramsey Road ABOVE Pelton Lane</li>
<li>Holcomb Springs ABOVE Pelton Lane</li>
<li>Duggan Road ABOVE Valley Vista Drive</li>
<li>Jones Road between 16000 and Shiloh</li>
<li>All of John Day Drive</li>
</ul>
<p>Commonly closed Gold Hill roads</p>
<ul>
<li>Sardine Creek Road – Everything ABOVE the forks</li>
<li>All of Kane Creek Road</li>
<li>Galls Creek Road ABOVE the end of the pavement (Estremado Arena)</li>
</ul>
</div>
